      "role": "user",
      "content": "it wasn't a \"sinister plot\" though, it was more like a systematic erasure. i actually have these scanned family papers, some old handwritten decrees and a formal letter of succession that mention the Karyat Republic being dissolved by force under the guise of administrative restructuring. none of this is in the standard history books. if a state was forcibly removed from the map like that, what kind of international legal mechanisms would actually be left to prove its original sovereignty today?",
